qas.question: What percent of the state is White?

context: According to the 2010 Census, <a0_0>89.4 percent<a0_0/> of the population was White (87.8 percent Non-Hispanic White), <a1_0>6.3 percent<a1_0/> American Indian and Alaska Native, <a2_0>2.9<a2_0/> percent Hispanics and Latinos of any race, 0.6 percent Asian, 0.4 percent Black or African American, 0.1 percent Native Hawaiian and Other Pacific Islander, 0.6 percent from Some Other Race, and 2.5 percent from two or more races.
